The protein was concentrated to 20 mg/ml and dialyzed against 5 mM HEPES, 2 mM MgCl2, 50 mM NaCl, 0.25 mM TCEP, 1 mM NaN3, pH 7.0, drop frozen as small pellets in liquid nitrogen and stored at -80 C.  The frozen concentrated protein was thawed and diluted to 10 mg/mL with 5 mM HEPES, 2 mM MgCl2, 1 mM NaN3, pH 7.5.  A stock solution of the peptide substrate L-Ala-L-Glu (Sigma) was neutralized to pH 7.5 with NaOH and brought to a final concentration of 1.6 M.
